column2: In last year’s election,the student body approved the Constitutional Clarity & Consistency Amendment 2015 to resolve current loopholes and inconsistencies in the ASUC Constitution,bring up to date the foundational document of the ASUC,simplify the document to be more accessible to students and leaders,and allow the ASUC to function more efficiently and equitably for long­term success. This amendment makes further technical changes to the Constitution to accomplish these goals. The language of the amendment,including footnotes describing the rationale for each change,is provided in the Elections Information Guide. Do you approve the ratification of the Constitutional Clarity & Consistency Amendment 2016?
column3: Proposition A: Constitutional Clarity & Consistency Amendment 2016
column4: The Ink Initiative Fee,a $2.50 per semester fee assessed to all students in the spring and fall semesters,would provide The Daily Californian,Berkeley’s independent newspaper,with the financial support necessary to (1) continue printing and distributing free newspapers across the campus and surrounding areas and (2) expand its online capacities (3) maintain itself as a training ground for UC Berkeley students in reporting,graphic and web design,and business operations. The Ink Initiative,subject to an annual inflation adjustment based on the San Francisco Area Consumer Price Index,would last for five years — beginning in fall 2017 and ending in spring 2022 — with 33 percent returning to financial aid for all students. It would not apply to students during the Summer Session. Do you approve this $2.50 semesterly fee?
column5: Proposition B: Ink Initiative Student Fee
column6: The existing $6.00 per student per semester The Green Initiative Fund (TGIF) Fee has awarded more than $2 million to 149 campus sustainability projects and over 240 student environmental internships since 2007. In order to continue funding impactful environmental sustainability projects,new student internships,and sustainability programming and initiatives through the Student Environmental Resource Center at UC Berkeley,do you approve the renewal and increase of The Green Initiative Fund Fee at $8.00 per student per semester?
column7: Proposition C: The Green Initiative Fund Student Fee
column8: Do you support the Declaration of and Action to Mitigate the Student Housing Crisis which:(1) Declares that UC Berkeley students are suffering from a housing crisis; and,(2) Demands the University of California,Berkeley work in good faith with the ASUC to build at least 6000 additional beds of student housing near campus and run by the university or a housing nonprofit (such as the Berkeley Student Cooperative) over the next 10 years; and,(3) Directs the ASUC to create and regularly update a comprehensive plan for addressing the student housing crisis?
column9: Proposition D: Declaration of and Action to Mitigate the Student Housing Crisis
